text=%25define=prerequisite apply=list bgcolor=#efefef border='1px solid black' padding-left=30px margin=0%25%0a%25define=recipeinfo color=black background-color=#f7f7f7 border='1px solid #cccccc' padding=4px%25%0a%25define=dllist color=black background-color=#f7f7f7 border='1px solid #cccccc' padding=4px%25%0a%0a*Option : Parameter(s) defined in the configuration file%0a*Addon : File(s) to be loaded separately%0a%0a!! SYSTEM%0a%0a:'''Page storage''' %25dlcol%25 : Flat files; no need for a database. Can handle thousands of pages. See [[Flat File Advantages]].%0a:'''[[requirements|'''Server Requirements''']]''' %25dlcol%25 : PHP 4.3.x minimum; can run in safe mode.  See [[Web Hosts]] and the [[(Cookbook:)Standalone]] Cookbook recipe.%0a:'''[[Upgrades]]''' %25dlcol%25 : By simply copying new version files or export from the Subversion repository%0a:'''[[Addons->PmWiki:Cookbook.Cookbook]]''' %25dlcol%25 : There are more than 200 [[(Cookbook:)Cookbook]] recipes. %0a%0a!! [[SECURITY->Security]]%0a%0a:'''SPAM protection''' %25dlcol%25 : By [[blocking words, IP addresses->Cookbook:Blocklist2]] (addon), and by limiting the quantity of [[non-approved URLs->UrlApprovals]]  (option), by [[encrypting the email address->Cookbook:DeObMail]] (addon)%0a:'''[[Passwords]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Page, group or site based, see also  [[PasswordsAdmin]]%0a:'''User authentication''' %25dlcol%25 : Available as an option ([[(PmWiki:)AuthUser]]) or an addon ([[(Cookbook:)UserAuth]]).%0a%0a!! FEATURES%0a%0a:'''[[Page editing->{$Name}?action=edit]]''' %25dlcol%25 : [[Similar->BasicEditing]] to others Wikis, has a [[button bar->Cookbook:GuiEdit]] (`PmWiki 2.0.beta16+) and preview. Handles [[simultaneous edits]]. Addon for [[spell checking->Cookbook:Spell checker]]%0a:'''[[Page history->{$Name}?action=diff]]''' %25dlcol%25 : History pages include Restore links. Configurable number of days of history.%0a:'''[[Free links->Links]] and [[WikiWord]]s''' %25dlcol%25 : [[WikiWord]] links are an option in version 2.1.  In previous releases they were enabled by default.%0a:'''[[Intersites links->InterMap]] ([=InterMap=])''' %25dlcol%25 : Configurable by the administrator or defined in the [[Site.InterMap]] page.%0a:'''[[(Wiki)Group]]s and hierarchy''' %25dlcol%25 : [[One level only->HierarchicalGroups]], handles menus and styling by groups, see [[Wiki architecture]]%0a:'''[[Categories]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Organise and find related pages with special Category markup.%0a:'''[[Navigation trails->WikiTrails]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Allow wiki authors to create "trails" through sequences of pages in the wiki.%0a:'''[[Search tools->Site.Search]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Search the entire site or the current group.  Administrator may exclude pages from appearing in search results. [[PageLists|Pre-defined searches]] are also available.%0a:'''[[Email-notification->Notify]] of revised pages''' %25dlcol%25 : Option, by admin, site based%0a:'''[[Web Feeds->PmWiki:WebFeeds]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Optional RSS, Atom, and Dublin Core syndication feeds as well as [[(Cookbook:)feed links]] to enable autodiscovery of the feeds%0a:'''Podcasting''' %25dlcol%25 : [[(PmWiki:)Web feed(s)]] enclosures are supported.%0a:'''[[International versions->Internationalizations]]''' %25dlcol%25 : See  [[Other languages]]. Handles accented characters and UTF-8.%0a:'''[[Page renaming->Cookbook:RenamePage]]''' %25dlcol%25 : addon%0a:'''[[(Cookbook:)Forms]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Forms may be embedded in wiki pages.%0a:'''Site Map''' %25dlcol%25 : Available via the [[PmWiki/Directives#pagelist|pagelists]] directive.%0a:'''[[(Cookbook:)Backlinks]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Available since version 2.0.beta33%0a%0a!! LAYOUT%0a%0a:'''[[(Skins:)Skins]]''' %25dlcol%25 : By admin, can be table or CSS based, addon for [[switching by users->Skins:SkinChange]] and [[interactive configuration->Skins:SkinConfig]]%0a:'''[[Layout modifications->LayoutBasics]]''' %25dlcol%25 : [[By admin-> LayoutBasics]] and by user, see [[group headers]]%0a:'''[[Printable layout->{$Name}?action=print]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Suppress menu, make link list and miscellaneous reformatting%0a:'''[[Style->WikiStyles]] and [[custom markup]]''' %25dlcol%25 :  %0a:'''[[Tables]]''' %25dlcol%25 : [[Tables]] and [[Table Directives]]%0a:'''[[(Cookbook:)Page table of contents]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Addon - see also [[(Cookbook:)numbered headers]]%0a:'''[[Inclusion->Directives#include]] in page''' %25dlcol%25 : Of others page (part or complete)%0a:'''[[Anchors->SpecialMarkups#MiscBracketAbuse]]''' %25dlcol%25 : In same or other page%0a:'''[[User uploaded attachments->Uploads]]''' %25dlcol%25 : [[Option to set->UploadsAdmin]] %0a:'''[[(Cookbook:)Images (auto) resizing]] and%0a[[galleries->Cookbook:SimpleGallery]]''' %25dlcol%25 : By addons, see also the category [[!images]] %0a:'''[[In browser drawing edit->Cookbook:PmWikiDraw]]''' %25dlcol%25 : By addon, need java enabled on browser.%0a:'''[[(Cookbook:)User Configurations|User preferences]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Option. See also the [[(Skins:)SkinChange]] add-on.%0a%0a!! HTML DETAILS%0a%0a:'''Handles HTML meta informations''' %25dlcol%25 : [[Keywords->Directives#keywords]] (site, group or page based), automatic noindex, nofollow for utility pages%0a:'''HTML compatibility''' %25dlcol%25 : XHTML 1.0 transitional, may differ for miscellaneous skins%0a:'''allow embedding of html in wiki pages''' %25dlcol%25 : [[Cookbook:enable HTML]]%0a:'''[[Browser caching->DebugVariables#EnableIMSCaching]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Option%0a:'''[[Nice URLs->PmWiki:Cookbook/CleanUrls]]''' %25dlcol%25 : See also $EnablePathInfo in LayoutVariables%0a:'''[[Hide e-mail addresses->Cookbook.DeObMail]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Addon%0a%0a!! MISCELLANEOUS ADDONS%0a%0a:'''Calendar ''' %25dlcol%25 : Each date becomes a wiki page. There are two possible implementations: [[WikiCalendar->PmWiki:Cookbook/WikiCalendar]] and [[PmCalendar->PmWiki:Cookbook/PmCalendar]]%0a:'''[[Latex in Wiki->PmWiki:Cookbook/MimeTeX]]''' %25dlcol%25 :  %0a:'''[[(Cookbook:)Publish (Wiki) trail]]s''' %25dlcol%25 :  %0a:'''Forum ''' %25dlcol%25 : There are 2 addons: [[(Cookbook:)Forum]] and [[(Cookbook:)SimpleForum]] %0a:'''[[(Cookbook:)Guestbook]]''' %25dlcol%25 :  %0a:'''For the full list ... ''' %25dlcol%25 : See the [[(Cookbook:)Cookbook]] recipes. %0a%0a!! ADMINISTRATION DETAILS%0a%0a:'''[[Wiki farms]]''' %25dlcol%25 : To have multiple wikis with a single installation of the wiki engine%0a:'''[[Missing and orphan pages search->RefCount]]''' %25dlcol%25 : Option - You can also list [[orphan and missing attachments->Cookbook:AttachlistEnhanced]] (addon)%0a:'''[[Handling of features requests and bug reports->PmWiki:PITS.PITS]]''' %25dlcol%25 :  %0a%0a!! LACKING (YET)%0a%0a:'''allow php scripts inside wiki''' %25dlcol%25 : like gunther.sf.net does - nah, too much of a security issue. A recipe for that is easy to implement... but who would be crazy enough to do it? ;)%0a:'''Publish as static pages''' %25dlcol%25 : Could be done, once we figure out how to control the caching; probably a set of recipes for specific types of wikis%0a:'''E-mail notification by page''' %25dlcol%25 : Easy: just enable [[Notify]] in the local/config of the page(s) you want to monitor.%0a:'''Interactive table editor''' %25dlcol%25 : If that means WYSIWYG-style editors, pmwiki's not the answer. At least currently.%0a%0aElements which are not listed as features and are a strength of PmWiki :%0a* Small code base (under 1 MB)%0a* A lot of parameters are handled by pages, without having the need to open system files, which greatly helps the Wiki administration.%0a* While there is only one major developer, there is a very active community and most addons are from independent people.%0a%0aAdd a new feature you would ''like'' to see in PmWiki as a new [[PITS]] entry marked ''Feature Request'', or use one of the [[mailing lists]] to brainstorm new features.%0a%0a(:title Features of PmWiki:)%0a
